Roman like Greek Comedy may be traced back to the Harvest‚ Vintage and other Festivals. ‘The joy of harvest' found expression in alternate verses, singer answering singer, at first playful, but gradually becoming so personal and bitter as finally to call lor the inter· lerence of the law. Hence sprang the versus Fescennini which are said to derive their name from the South Etrurian town Fescennium. Their metre was the Saturnian, the one national Roman product in matters rhythmical‚ a mixture of the iambic and trochaic rhythm.
